#######################
## Initialization

DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
	"PG.pl",
	"PGbasicmacros.pl",
	"PGanswermacros.pl",
	"PGcourse.pl"
	);

TEXT(beginproblem());

###################################
# Setup

$a = random(2,9,1);
$b = random(2,9,1);
$c = random(2,9,1);

###################################
# Main text

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
Give values of \(C\) and \(R\) so that 
\[ $a \ | $b \ x + $c|<1\]
is equivalent to
\[ |x-C|<R.\] $BR $BR
\(C=\) \{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR $BR
\(R=\) \{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

###################################
## Answer evaluation

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$ans1 = -$c/$b;
$ans2 = 1/($a*$b);

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

ENDDOCUMENT();
